Hi.
I have a DELL P1110 monitor (CRT, 21 inch, 2 VGA inputs). I can confirm, that 
it basicaly clone of (SUN-GDM-5410 or rather Compaq P1100)

Plug and Play ID: DEL50AB [DELL P1100]

also additional misconvergence controls (top and bottom) works as expected, 
that ones commented out (in database from 20061014)

<control id="vtopmisconvergence" address="0xf6"/>
<control id="vbotmisconvergence" address="0xf7"/>

Control at address 0xf5 is responsible for controling "Color presed mode" 
option

with values
0 - Easy
1 - Expert
2 - sRGB

Control at address 0xe0 trigers "Auto sizing and centering" feature.

Control at address 0xe2 controls "Control Return" Feature of this monitor 
(availble after monitor warmup).


--Boundary-00=_wsX4FODrqzrw69+
Content-Type: text/xml;
  charset="utf-8";
  name="DEL50AB.xml"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: attachment;
	filename="DEL50AB.xml"

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!---DELL P1100 is a CRT. CAPS invalid
(prot(monitor)  type(crt) model( DELAB50           edid bin(128(################################################################################################################################))cmds(01020304050608090A0B0C4F)vcp(00010810121416181A20222426283032384042445456686C6E70E0E2F1F2F3F4F5F6F7)
-->
<monitor name="DELL P1100" init="standard">
	<include file="SUN0577"/>
	<controls>
	    <control id="autosizingandcentering" address="0xe0" />
	    <control id="colorreturn" address="0xe2" />
	    
	    <control id="colorpresetmode" address="0xf5">
		<value id="easy" value="0" />
		<value id="expert" value="1" />
		<value id="srgb" value="2" />
	    </control>
	    <control id="vtopmisconvergence" address="0xf6" />
	    <control id="vbotmisconvergence" address="0xf7" />
	</controls>
</monitor>

--Boundary-00=_wsX4FODrqzrw69+--


